@Gezus82 If I'm not mistaking, it does work with kicker and X mana cost (a copy also copies the mode of the card, X among other things). It will create only one additionnal copy of spell with storm, since the storm copies are not being cast, they're being put directly onto the stack.

It's te same way as storm does not count previous storm copies. For instance, if you play a brain freeze after playing a ponder and a brainstorm, it will create 2 copy, for a total of 12 cards milled, if you play a second brainfreeze, it will only create 3 copy for a total of 16 cards, it won't count the first 2 copy.

I hope I haven't mislead you and that you we're able to understand what I meant!
